    "updated_at": "2024-02-22T18:18:03Z",
    "body": "I was having the same issue. Mine was a very specific use case.\r\n\r\nI'm using [poetry](https://python-poetry.org) to manage dependencies and virtualenvs.\r\n\r\nIn my poetry configuration I had the [virtualenv prompt option](https://python-poetry.org/docs/configuration/#virtualenvsprompt) set to empty string (`virtualenvs.prompt = \"\"`), which would create a `pyvenv.cfg` config with `prompt = `, and [starship will read and use if set](https://github.com/starship/starship/blob/1082afce0a27c5459d25998ea137067eb44dadab/src/modules/python.rs#L124-L130).\r\n\r\nThe solution was to add something useful to `virtualenvs.prompt` (like the default value).",
